  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Responding to Mitigating the Effects of the COVID-19 Pandemic in Sudan through Better Coordination, Improved Hygiene and Sanitation, and Safer Points of Entry</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The aim of this project is to respond to the current effects, and mitigate the future impact, of the current COVID-19 pandemic in Sudan, particularly on vulnerable populations and migrants, in alignment with the four strategic priorities outlined under IOM&apos;s Global Strategic Preparedness and Response Plan (SPRP). The objective of the project contributes to the prevention of COVID-19 and mitigation of its negative impacts on migrants and vulnerable populations by improving coordination of the COVID-19 response through better, more timely information, improving and rehabilitating key water, sanitation and hygiene (WASH) facilities, and improving the safety of Points of Entry (PoE).</narrative>
  </description>
